As part of our automation framework migration, we have implemented a DBRouter component that executes parameterised SQL queries at runtime against BISS_DATA and BISS_INET. All test data is now resolved dynamically per execution — no static herd numbers or usernames exist anywhere in the test scripts.

To support this, we need the following queries validated and provided. Each query must return both a herd number (from BISS_DATA) and a corresponding agent login ID (from BISS_INET via tdco_customer_asscs / tdcr_user_info). The agent login is resolved separately using the herd number as the join key.

Transfers Module

1. Agent — Herds with available entitlements (agent-managed)
Required columns: herd_no, agent_login_id
Criteria:

	•	Herd has active entitlements (tdbs_entitlement or equivalent) for the current scheme year
	•	Herd is associated with an active agent via tdco_customer_asscs (ca_cac_code = 194, SYSDATE BETWEEN ca_start_date AND ca_end_date)
	•	Agent login resolvable from tdcr_user_info via uri_ccs_bus_id
	•	Excludes herds with no land parcels and herds with payment already processed

2. Individual — Herds with available entitlements (individual login)
Required columns: herd_no, individual_login_id
Criteria:

	•	Same entitlement conditions as above
	•	Login resolved via individual role (bcus_role_code = 115) not agent role
	•	bcus_role_code = 100 for the herd, 115 for the login user

3. ETF (Entitlement Transfer Form) — Herds associated with an ETF with available entitlements
Required columns: herd_no, agent_login_id, etf_reference (if applicable)
Criteria:

	•	Herd has an active or pending ETF record for the current scheme year
	•	Entitlements available for transfer (not fully allocated)
	•	Agent login resolvable as above

NR/CISYF Module

4. Not Started — Agent login + herd where application has not been initiated
Required columns: herd_no, agent_login_id
Criteria:

	•	mde_abbrev = 'RI' on vwbs_application_herd (Not Started / preprint only)
	•	Herd is CISYF-eligible: NVL((SELECT pkbs_payment_utils.fn_GetSchemeApplied(aph_app_id, 3) FROM dual), 'N') = 'Y'
	•	At least one non-deleted land parcel exists (tdbs_application_land, apl_deleted_ind = 'N')
	•	No payment processed (tdbs_payment_application, pap_payment_ind = 'Y' absent)
	•	SUBSTR(app_herd_no, 1, 1) > 'A' to exclude TRN reference numbers
	•	Agent login resolvable from BISS_INET via tdco_customer_asscs

5. In Progress / Editable — Agent login + herd where application is initiated but not submitted
Required columns: herd_no, agent_login_id
Criteria:

	•	mde_abbrev = 'D' (Draft) or mde_abbrev = 'DD' (Draft Dept) on vwbs_application_herd
	•	Same land parcel and CISYF eligibility conditions as above
	•	Agent login resolvable from BISS_INET

6. Submitted — Agent login + herd where application has been successfully submitted
Required columns: herd_no, agent_login_id
Criteria:

	•	mde_abbrev = 'I' (iNet Submitted) on vwbs_application_herd
	•	CISYF scheme applied: same fn_GetSchemeApplied check
	•	Agent login resolvable from BISS_INET

Notes for the DB team:

	•	All queries must be parameterised by app_year (current = 2026)
	•	fn_GetSchemeApplied must be wrapped in a scalar subquery (SELECT ... FROM dual) to prevent ORA-06503 on certain aph_app_id values
	•	Results must be randomisable (ORDER BY DBMS_RANDOM.VALUE) so different data is returned per execution
	•	A ROWNUM <= N limit parameter is required so the framework can control pool size
	•	Agent login resolution always queries BISS_INET — herd data always queries BISS_DATA

